WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.160
[Amit Varma]: If you're a writer or a filmmaker or a musician or a photographer, bloody hell, what a time

00:00:10.160 --> 00:00:15.200
[Amit Varma]: to be alive. We live in a golden age for creators. And this is clear when I think back, say,

00:00:15.200 --> 00:00:20.480
[Amit Varma]: just 25 years. In 1995, when I was a writer, I had to attempt to please third parties to

00:00:20.480 --> 00:00:25.240
[Amit Varma]: get my work out there. If I wrote articles, I had to submit them to newspapers or magazines.

00:00:25.240 --> 00:00:29.280
[Amit Varma]: They were gatekeepers in my way. Even if I got through them, the formats in which I could

00:00:29.280 --> 00:00:33.720
[Amit Varma]: write were fixed. The pay was a pittance, always coming through intermediaries who sold

00:00:33.720 --> 00:00:37.920
[Amit Varma]: eyeballs for advertising. There was no way I could connect directly with my audience

00:00:37.920 --> 00:00:42.680
[Amit Varma]: or even capture some of the value that I brought into their lives. Because the possibilities

00:00:42.680 --> 00:00:48.360
[Amit Varma]: were limited, many of the things I could have done were left undone, unimagined, and therefore

00:00:48.360 --> 00:00:54.400
[Amit Varma]: unseen. But between then and now, all those restrictions have vanished. Creators of

00:00:54.400 --> 00:00:58.960
[Amit Varma]: all sorts have the means of production and distribution in their hands. They can play

00:00:58.960 --> 00:01:03.000
[Amit Varma]: with different forms, they can connect with their audiences, they can form communities

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:07.960
[Amit Varma]: of those audiences, and they can get paid directly. This is so miraculous. And for someone

00:01:07.960 --> 00:01:14.680
[Amit Varma]: like me, so exciting. I'm speaking into my microphone right now, directly to you. There's

00:01:14.680 --> 00:01:18.920
[Unknown]: no one between us.

00:01:18.920 --> 00:01:24.320
[Unknown]: Welcome to The Seen and The Unseen, our weekly podcast on economics, politics and behavioral

00:01:24.320 --> 00:01:31.440
[Unknown]: science. Please welcome your host, Amit Bharma.

00:01:31.440 --> 00:01:34.760
[Amit Varma]: Welcome to The Seen and The Unseen. If you're a creator, then there are many, many lessons

00:01:34.760 --> 00:01:39.960
[Amit Varma]: to learn from my guest today, Roshan Abbas. Roshan, in a sense, was a new age creator

00:01:39.960 --> 00:01:44.880
[Amit Varma]: in the old world before the new age. He started with theatre, became a radio superstar in

00:01:44.880 --> 00:01:49.560
[Amit Varma]: the 1990s, moved on to television and rocked that scene, took his destiny into his own

00:01:49.560 --> 00:01:54.760
[Amit Varma]: hands by starting an events management company called Encompass, made that big, sold it,

00:01:54.760 --> 00:01:59.280
[Amit Varma]: wrote a play, made a feature film, wrote a couple of books, invested in a bunch of successful

00:01:59.280 --> 00:02:05.080
[Amit Varma]: creator startups, and began Commune, a performance arts collective that has launched many careers.

00:02:05.080 --> 00:02:09.540
[Amit Varma]: He didn't stick to one thing. He never ossified, which is the reason that his insights on this

00:02:09.540 --> 00:02:14.920
[Amit Varma]: creator economy are so enlightening. I first came into direct contact with Roshan when

00:02:14.920 --> 00:02:18.920
[Amit Varma]: he signed up for my online course, The Art of Clear Writing, and I've learned a lot from

00:02:18.920 --> 00:02:22.880
[Amit Varma]: all our interactions since. In fact, just last weekend, I held a session for the alumni

00:02:22.880 --> 00:02:27.800
[Amit Varma]: of my course on this brave new world for creators. It lasted three and a half hours, almost like

00:02:27.800 --> 00:02:32.760
[Amit Varma]: a seen unseen episode, and many creators, including Roshan, shared their learning there.

00:02:32.760 --> 00:02:37.560
[Amit Varma]: I was so charged by that session that I couldn't sleep all night. What an exciting world we

00:02:37.560 --> 00:02:42.400
[Amit Varma]: live in. And what a lovely conversation I had with Roshan when I invited him for this

00:02:42.400 --> 00:02:47.220
[Amit Varma]: episode. Before we get to it, though, a quick plug, registration is now open for the September

00:02:47.220 --> 00:02:52.160
[Amit Varma]: cohort of The Art of Clear Writing. Head on over to indiauncut.com slash clear writing

00:02:52.160 --> 00:02:58.440
[Amit Varma]: to register. And now a quick commercial break before Roshan Ambass takes the floor.

